ltaub%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20some%20airports%20have%20long%20security%20lines%2C%20and%20others%20are%20a%20breeze%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TSA%20employee%20and%20long%20lines%20at%20LGA%20airport%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2ee955b58f1f0f9336c17%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20TSA%20agent%20watches%20passengers%20queue%20to%20go%20through%20security%20at%20New%20York's%20LaGuardia%20airport.%3Cp%3ECHARLY%20TRIBALLEAU%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETSA%20callout%20rates%20at%20some%20major%20airports%20are%20up%20to%2040%25%2C%20while%20smaller%20airports%20remain%20unscathed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEmployees%20have%20missed%20weeks%20of%20pay%20due%20to%20the%20partial%20government%20shutdown.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHere's%20why%20security%20lines%20at%20some%20airports%20are%20worse%20than%20others.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAtlanta%20TSA%20officer%20Aaron%20Barker%20knows%20that%20for%20travelers%2C%20the%20length%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsa-lines-atlanta-houston-united-delta-waive-change-fees-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eairport%20security%20line%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20feel%20like%20a%20roll%20of%20the%20dice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-ice-agents-paid-tsa-not-dhs-government-shutdown-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epartial%20government%20shutdown%3C%2Fa%3E%20drags%20on%2C%20however%2C%20a%20few%20key%20factors%20influence%20why%20the%20officer%20callout%20rate%20at%20Houston's%20Hobby%20is%2040%25%2C%20for%20example%2C%20while%20operations%20at%20smaller%20airports%20remain%20business%20as%20usual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDaycare%20fees%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20gas%2C%20and%20things%20like%20that%20are%20different%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country%2C%26quot%3B%20Barker%2C%20an%20American%20Federation%20of%20Government%20Employees%20local%20president%2C%20said%20at%20the%20union's%20press%20conference%20on%20Tuesday.%20The%20TSA%20officer%20callout%20rate%20at%20his%20airport%20is%20one%20of%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20country%20at%2037%25.%20%26quot%3BMost%20officers%20cannot%20afford%20to%20live%20in%20Atlanta%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20they're%20living%20an%20hour%2C%20sometimes%20an%20hour-and-a-half%20away%20from%20work%20and%20need%20to%20commute.%20That's%20probably%20why%20you%20may%20see%20a%20big%20difference%20in%20larger%20airports.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TSA%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20average%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairport-lines-tsa-agents-flight-delays-jfk-nola-spring-break-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enational%20callout%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20reached%20nearly%2012%25%20on%20Monday%2C%20March%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20than%20450%20TSA%20officers%20quit%20and%20thousands%20have%20called%20out%20sick%20from%20work%20because%20they%20are%20not%20able%20to%20afford%20gas%2C%20childcare%2C%20food%2C%20or%20rent%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Lauren%20Bis%2C%20the%20acting%20assistant%20secretary%20for%20public%20affairs%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security.%20The%20Trump%20administration%20has%20deployed%20Immigration%20and%20Customs%20Agents%20to%20%26quot%3Bhelp%20bolster%20TSA%20efforts%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20the%20workers'%20union%20says%20these%20ICE%20officers%20are%20%26quot%3Buntrained%26quot%3B%20and%20should%20not%20replace%20TSA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20dove%20into%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclear-surging-searches-airport-security-delays-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estaffing%20shortages%20and%20wait%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%20vary%20widely%20between%20airports%20%E2%80%94%20and%20what%20travelers%20can%20expect%20going%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHave%20a%20story%20to%20tell%20about%20travel%20during%20the%20partial%20government%20shutdown%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aallisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Atrains%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrains%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2252b32af2-8dc1-4219-bb74-80eedc6e3c09%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBurnout%20is%20big%20at%20major%20airports%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthese-20-airports-dont-use-tsa-screeners-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMajor%20US%20airports%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20like%20Chicago%20O'Hare%2C%20Phoenix%2C%20Pittsburgh%2C%20and%20New%20York-JFK%20%E2%80%94%20are%20seeing%20notably%20higher%20staff%20callouts%20than%20smaller%20airports.%20TSA%20officers%20(TSOs)%20received%20their%20first%20%240%20paycheck%20in%20mid-March%20after%20DHS%20funding%20lapsed%20on%20February%2014%20and%20they%20started%20working%20without%20pay.%20This%20means%20bank%20accounts%20are%20stretched%20especially%20thin%20for%20staff%20living%20in%20higher%20cost-of-living%20cities.%20Workers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20call%20out%20if%20they%20can't%20afford%20childcare%20or%20transportation%20to%20and%20from%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20union%2C%20TSA%20officers%20at%20various%20locations%20said%20staff%20at%20smaller%20airports%20have%20received%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcasinos-donating-food-tsa-agents-las-vegas-airport-government-shutdown-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20donations%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20both%20monetary%20and%20food%20%E2%80%94%20to%20supplement%20their%20paychecks%20because%20the%20communities%20in%20rural%20areas%20tend%20to%20know%20local%20workers%20personally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsa-wait-times-airports-with-longest-delays-how-to-check-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etravel%20volume%20plays%20a%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too.%20Major%20airports%20service%20larger%20planes%20and%20significantly%20more%20people%20on%20a%20daily%20basis.%20Some%20of%20these%20airports%20may%20also%20serve%20as%20hubs%20for%20major%20airlines%2C%20meaning%20they%20handle%20many%20connecting%20flights%20in%20addition%20to%20direct%20traffic.%20For%20example%2C%20Delta%20in%20Atlanta%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspent-four-hours-at-tsa-jfk-the-situation-felt-dangerous-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJetBlue%20at%20New%20York's%20JFK%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20United%20at%20Houston's%20IAH.%20All%20of%20these%20airports%20are%20seeing%20officer%20callout%20rates%20over%2030%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLarger%20hub%20airports%20are%20feeling%20the%20pressure%20more%20acutely%20because%20they%20have%20constant%2C%20steady%20streams%20of%20passengers%2C%20with%20rarely%20any%20lulls%20where%20the%20security%20line%20empties%20out%20the%20way%20you%20might%20see%20at%20a%20small%20regional%20airport%2C%26quot%3B%20Sally%20French%2C%20co-host%20of%20NerdWallet's%20%26quot%3BSmart%20Travel%26quot%3B%20podcast%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20understaffed%20at%20a%20major%20hub%2C%20a%20long%20line%20only%20gets%20longer%20because%20there's%20never%20that%20natural%20break%20in%20passenger%20flow%20that%20allows%20things%20to%20catch%20up.%20It's%20a%20compounding%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20partial%20shutdown%20is%20happening%20at%20a%20busy%20time%20of%20year%20for%20air%20travel.%20Many%20big-city%20airports%20are%20busy%20because%20of%20spring%20breakers%3B%20the%20US%20Travel%20Association%20estimated%20a%20record%20171%20million%20people%20will%20fly%20in%20the%20US%20in%20March%20and%20April.%20Travelers%20should%20expect%20longer%20lines%20on%20peak%20days%2C%20such%20as%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f627592-b451-416f-b3c9-e1281c011b53%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAirport%20policies%20are%20having%20an%20impact%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20travel%20volume%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmass-tsa-delays-absences-flying-unpredictable-long-lines-wait-times-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esecurity%20wait%20times%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20also%20be%20shaped%20by%20individual%20airport%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20airports%2C%20like%20San%20Francisco%20International%20and%20Orlando%20Sanford%20International%2C%20use%20private%20contractors%20instead%20of%20TSA%20screeners%2C%20which%20airports%20say%20helps%20ease%20wait%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20airports%20have%20a%20big%20share%20of%20workers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftsa-workers-could-miss-another-paycheck-partial-government-shutdown-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eliving%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20might%20lean%20on%20temporary%2C%20more%20predictable%20sources%20of%20income%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20until%20their%20TSA%20paychecks%20resume.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20reports%20of%20food%20drives%20at%20airports%20for%20these%20employees%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20are%20supplementing%20their%20income%20by%20driving%20for%20rideshare%20services%2C%20picking%20up%20retail%20shifts%20or%20doing%20gig%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20French%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnion%20leaders%20said%20that%20airport%20management%20varies%20in%20how%20they%20handle%20furloughs%2C%20PTO%2C%20and%20time-off%20policies.%20TSA%20workers%20are%20legally%20required%20to%20work%20without%20pay%20during%20a%20shutdown%2C%20and%20some%20employees%20feel%20their%20job%20security%20or%20chance%20at%20backpay%20is%20under%20greater%20threat%20if%20they%20call%20out%20because%20of%20their%20specific%20location.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20some%20airports%20in%20my%20region%20who%20are%20applying%20it%20in%20the%20most%20extreme%20measure%2C%20so%20that%20across%20the%20board%2C%20everybody%20has%20to%20follow%20the%20same%20strictest%20part%20of%20the%20policy%20in%20order%20to%20get%20time%20off%20during%20this%2C%20whereas%20some%20other%20airports%20follow%20the%20minimum%20portion%20of%20that%20policy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Duncan%20McGuire%2C%20another%20TSA%20worker%20in%20Portland%20and%20a%20union%20vice%20president%20for%20several%20western%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20some%20TSOs%20are%20nearing%20retirement%20and%20that%20their%20benefits%2C%20earned%20over%20decades%20of%20service%2C%20are%20so%20good%20that%20there%20is%20no%20reason%20to%20quit%20during%20the%20shutdown%20to%20try%20to%20start%20over%20somewhere%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20TSA%20workers%20are%20back%20on%20payroll%2C%20French%20said%20travelers%20can%20continue%20to%20expect%20hourslong%20security%20lines.%20Next%20week%2C%20many%20employees%20will%20receive%20their%20April%20rent%2C%20childcare%2C%20and%20car%20invoices%2C%20which%20could%20prompt%20more%20workers%20to%20call%20off%20work.%20Union%20leaders%20said%20many%20workers%20have%20already%20quit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20bad%20news%20for%20travelers%20and%20for%20airlines'%20bottom%20line%2C%20French%20said%2C%20because%20%26quot%3Bthe%20travel%20industry%20thrives%20on%20consumer%20confidence%2C%20and%20right%20now%2C%20that%20confidence%20seems%20to%20be%20shaky.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarlos%20Rodriguez%2C%20a%20TSO%20and%20a%20union%20leader%20in%20the%20northeast%2C%20said%20he%20and%20his%20colleagues%20are%20doing%20their%20best%20to%20keep%20America%20moving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20love%20my%20city%2C%20I%20love%20my%20country%2C%20but%20most%20importantly%2C%20I%20love%20the%20great%20men%20and%20women%20of%20TSA%20who%20I%20serve%20with%20every%20day%2C%20fulfilling%20our%20oath%20to%20protect%20people%20and%20freedom%20of%20movement%20and%20commerce%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20really%20difficult%20to%20do%20that%20when%20we%20don't%20know%20who's%20protecting%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-big-airports-tsa-worker-shortage-long-waits-government-shutdown-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774386470000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2eea358b5806618e7df4d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-big-airports-tsa-worker-shortage-long-waits-government-shutdown-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22TSA%20callout%20rates%20at%20some%20airports%20are%20up%20to%2040%25%2C%20while%20others%20are%20running%20smoothly.%20Here's%20why.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly%2CTaylor%20Rains)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-big-airports-tsa-worker-shortage-long-waits-government-shutdown-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Having%203%20young%20kids%20left%20my%20husband%20and%20me%20exhausted%20and%20disconnected.%20This%20is%20what%20we%20did%20to%20feel%20like%20a%20team%20again.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Family%20poising%20for%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b32ae8a96e437d6eb83dfd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20and%20her%20husband%20have%20three%20kids%20under%203.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERaising%20three%20kids%20under%20three%20left%20us%20exhausted%20and%20emotionally%20disconnected.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20started%20quietly%20keeping%20score%20of%20who%20was%20doing%20more%20at%20home.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESaying%20%26quot%3Bthank%20you%26quot%3B%20daily%20helped%20us%20feel%20like%20teammates%20again.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-shares-why-she-chose-a-faraway-preschool-for-kid-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eday%20care%20closures%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20spent%20nine%20hours%20at%20home%20with%20the%20kids%20(without%20setting%20foot%20outside)%20while%20my%20husband%20went%20to%20work.%20In%20that%20time%2C%20I%20changed%20countless%20poopy%20diapers%2C%20served%20infinite%20snacks%2C%20ran%20up%20and%20down%20the%20stairs%20trying%20to%20get%20the%20kids%20to%20nap%2C%20and%20cleaned%20up%20the%20same%20messes%20over%20and%20over%20again%20with%20our%20three%20kids%2C%20ages%203%20and%20under.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20my%20husband%20spent%20his%20day%20at%20work%20trying%20to%20catch%20up%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmichelin-star-chefs-lunch-recipes-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworking%20straight%20through%20lunch%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20he%20could%20make%20it%20back%20home%20ASAP%20to%20help%20me%20with%20the%20evening%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20work%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-little-kids-can-be-exhausting-and-stressful-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecaring%20for%20our%20young%20children%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20don't%20have%20much%20time%20to%20connect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222792a1f9-b859-4736-8982-77bf554c4567%5C%22%3EWe%20don't%20have%20energy%20for%20our%20relationship%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20days%2C%20neither%20my%20husband%20nor%20I%20has%20the%20energy%20to%20connect%20after%20getting%20the%20kids%20fed%2C%20bathed%2C%20and%20in%20bed.%20Our%20conversations%20immediately%20turn%20to%20the%20logistics%20of%20the%20next%20day%3A%20who's%20going%20to%20drop%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-you-are-choosing-a-bad-daycare-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ekids%20off%20at%20day%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20the%20bags%20packed%2C%20does%20someone%20need%20to%20go%20to%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20should%20we%20call%20a%20handyman%20about%20the%20leaky%20faucet%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221110%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20kids%20together%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b32c514d65ec517529efb5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22696%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20to-dos%20add%20up%2C%20so%20does%20the%20temptation%20to%20keep%20score.%20We%20settle%20into%20a%20competitive%20mindset%20where%20we%20constantly%20evaluate%20who's%20doing%20more%20%E2%80%94%20slowly%20building%20resentment%20and%20discontent.%20Remembering%20that%20we're%20both%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteammates-before-married-relationship-is-stronger-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20same%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20same%20goal%20of%20caring%20for%20our%20family%20can%20feel%20far-fetched.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20no%20wonder%2C%20then%2C%20why%20marriage%20satisfaction%20rates%20decline%20after%20children%2C%20with%20increased%20dissatisfaction%20among%20parents%20with%20more%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20first%20lady%20Michelle%20Obama%20spoke%20of%20this%20trend%20when%20she%20described%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmichelle-obama-pet-peeve-husband-barack-former-president-punctuality-late-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erelationship%20with%20Barack%20Obama%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20early%20years%20of%20their%20children's%20lives%2C%20saying%20she%20%26quot%3Bcouldn't%20stand%26quot%3B%20her%20husband%20for%20about%2010%20years%20and%20noting%20that%20%26quot%3Bmarriage%20is%20never%2050%2F50.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2d9c0b5-e7dc-408a-bec1-45df95a2a3aa%5C%22%3EWe%20thank%20each%20other%20as%20much%20as%20possible%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20practice%20that%20has%20helped%20my%20husband%20and%20me%20weather%20this%20chaotic%20season%20is%20saying%20%26quot%3Bthank%20you%26quot%3B%20to%20each%20other%20as%20often%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThank%20you%20for%20doing%20those%20dishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThank%20you%20for%20taking%20out%20the%20trash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThank%20you%20for%20planning%20that%20meal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThank%20you%20for%20prepping%20the%20bottles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20for%20handling%20the%20bedtime%20routine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20for%20packing%20the%20day%20care%20bags.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20for%20changing%20that%20diaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDo%20I%20really%20need%20to%20thank%20my%20husband%20for%20taking%20out%20the%20trash%3F%20At%20first%2C%20it%20may%20sound%20trivial.%20Is%20it%20really%20necessary%20to%20thank%20my%20spouse%20for%20doing%20the%20mundane%20chores%20that%20keep%20our%20family%20running%3F%20Isn't%20the%20%26quot%3Bthank%20you%26quot%3B%20understood%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpressing%20gratitude%20for%20specific%20tasks%20challenges%20us%20to%20take%20note%20of%20the%20other%20person's%20contributions%2C%20which%20are%20often%20overlooked.%20It's%20easy%20to%20forget%20that%20the%20sink%20was%20once%20full%20of%20dishes%20when%20it's%20suddenly%20clean%20again%20(and%20already%20being%20refilled%20with%20more%20dirty%20dishes).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20thanks%20me%20for%20grocery%20shopping%20and%20meal%20planning%2C%20it%20lets%20me%20know%20he%20notices%2C%20values%2C%20and%20respects%20my%20contributions%20to%20our%20household.%20Even%20though%20the%20work%20seems%20commonplace%2C%20it%20still%20requires%20time%20and%20energy%20on%20my%20part.%20When%20he%20recognizes%20my%20efforts%2C%20he's%20also%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20%3Cem%3Esee%3C%2Fem%3E%20you%2C%20and%20I%20know%20how%20hard%20you're%20working.%26quot%3B%20It's%20a%20small%20gesture%20that%20goes%20a%20long%20way%20in%20making%20me%20feel%20loved%20and%20appreciated.%20It%20also%20reaffirms%20that%20we're%20in%20this%20thing%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20when%20I%20thank%20my%20husband%20for%20emptying%20the%20smelly%20diaper%20pails%2C%20managing%20toddler%20bathtime%2C%20and%20organizing%20our%20tax%20documents%2C%20I'm%20also%20saying%20%26quot%3BThank%20you%20for%20shouldering%20this%20part%20of%20the%20load%20to%20make%20things%20lighter%20for%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5c4a24b-e9c7-4100-a16d-9be668177254%5C%22%3EThe%20littlest%20gestures%20can%20have%20the%20largest%20impact%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20small%20moments%20of%20connection%20have%20been%20our%20cozy%20refuge%20amid%20life's%20recurring%20blizzards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20nature%20reveals%2C%20some%20seasons%20are%20simply%20about%20survival.%20We%20let%20go%20of%20everything%20extraneous%20(like%20lavish%20date%20nights%20and%20big%20vacations)%2C%20hunker%20down%20and%20endure%20with%20the%20bare%20necessities%20%E2%80%94%20trusting%20in%20brighter%20days%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Couple%20skiing.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b4143e4d65ec517529f4fc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20thanks%20her%20spouse%20for%20everything%20they%20do%20to%20stay%20connected.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20season%20lasts%20forever.%20Even%20the%20coldest%20winters%20eventually%20yield%20to%20spring.%20A%20few%20years%20of%20difficult%20times%20and%20disconnection%20don't%20necessarily%20mean%20a%20bad%20marriage%20or%20that%20the%20relationship%20is%20doomed.%20Withstanding%20the%20tough%20times%20together%20can%20strengthen%20bonds%2C%20as%20long%20as%20you%20commit%20to%20small%20practices%20%E2%80%94%20like%20saying%20thank%20you%20%E2%80%94%20to%20keep%20you%20tethered%20to%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-resentment-marriage-gratitude-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774386421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69b32b04a7a4f9df67ba4434%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-resentment-marriage-gratitude-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20three%20kids%20under%20three%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20felt%20resentment%20creeping%20in.%20Saying%20%26quot%3Bthank%20you%26quot%3B%20changed%20everything.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Lauren%20Salles%20Gumpert)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparenting-resentment-marriage-gratitude-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22OpenAI%20is%20scrapping%20the%20Sora%20app%20to%20chase%20bigger%20AI%20goals%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Sora%20by%20OpenAI%20logo%20appears%20on%20the%20app%20store.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2f14c58b5806618e7df6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20is%20discontinuing%20Sora%2C%20its%20AI%20text-to-video%20generator.%3Cp%3EIllustration%20by%20Thomas%20Fuller%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20announced%20it%20is%20discontinuing%20its%20viral%20video%20app%20Sora.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20plans%20to%20focus%20on%20robotics%20to%20solve%20%26quot%3Breal-world%2C%20physical%20tasks%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESora's%20demise%20followed%20its%20lead%20staffer's%20description%20of%20the%20project's%20economics%20as%20%26quot%3Bunsustainable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20is%20pulling%20the%20plug%20on%20the%20Sora%20app%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20in%20the%20current%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20confirmed%20it%20will%20discontinue%20Sora%20as%20a%20consumer%20app%20and%20API%2C%20marking%20a%20sharp%20pivot%20away%20from%20one%20of%20its%20splashiest%20generative%20video%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20decided%20to%20discontinue%20Sora%20in%20the%20consumer%20app%20and%20API%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20OpenAI%20spokesperson%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20we%20focus%20and%20compute%20demand%20grows%2C%20the%20Sora%20research%20team%20continues%20to%20focus%20on%20world%20simulation%20research%20to%20advance%20robotics%20that%20will%20help%20people%20solve%20real-world%2C%20physical%20tasks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discontinuation%20is%20a%20notable%20turn%20for%20a%20product%20that%20once%20embodied%20OpenAI's%20creative%20ambitions.%20When%20Sora%20launched%20in%20late%20September%202025%2C%20it%20quickly%20went%20viral%20for%20generating%20realistic%2C%20cinematic%20video%20clips%20from%20text%20prompts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TikTok-esque%20app%20hit%20No.%201%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenais-sora-hits-no-1-spot-on-apple-app-store-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EApple's%20App%20Store%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20hit%201%20million%20downloads%20in%20under%20five%20days%2C%20according%20to%20October%20posts%20from%20Sora%20lead%20Bill%20Peebles%2C%20who%20described%20%26quot%3Bsurging%20growth%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20team%20raced%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeadaches%20began%20almost%20as%20quickly%20as%20the%20hypetrain%20took%20off.%20OpenAI%20had%20to%20introduce%20guardrails%20after%20users%20generated%20videos%20of%20protected%20intellectual%20property%2C%20such%20as%20Pok%C3%A9mon's%20Pikachu%20in%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-sora-intellectual-property-video-response-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESaving%20Private%20Ryan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20of%20historical%20figures%20like%20Martin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20Cameo%2C%20the%20short-form%20video%20app%20where%20users%20can%20pay%20for%20personalized%20messages%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcameo-lawsuit-openai-copyright-infringement-sora-app-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esued%20OpenAI%20for%20trademark%20infringement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20OpenAI%20named%20one%20of%20the%20Sora%20app's%20core%20features%20%26quot%3Bcameo.%26quot%3B%20(OpenAI%20later%20changed%20the%20name%20of%20the%20feature.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20doubled%20down%2C%20saying%20that%20IP%20rights%20holders%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20to%20scrap%20Sora%20comes%20as%20OpenAI%20is%20increasingly%20focused%20on%20core%20products%20as%20it%20attempts%20to%20make%20money%20ahead%20of%20a%20potential%20IPO.%20In%20August%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffidji-simo-openai-product-research-profitability-profile-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECEO%20Sam%20Altman%20hired%20Fidji%20Simo%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%2040-year-old%20former%20Instacart%20CEO%20and%20longtime%20Meta%20executive%2C%20to%20become%20the%20company's%20product%20head.%20She%20and%20the%20company%20are%20tasked%20with%20ensuring%20their%20powerful%20models%20can%20sustain%20the%20enormous%20cost%20of%20training%20and%20deployment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20miss%20this%20moment%20because%20we%20are%20distracted%20by%20side%20quests%2C%26quot%3B%20Simo%20told%20employees%20at%20an%20all-hands%20meeting%2C%20according%20to%20a%20person%20familiar%20with%20her%20remarks.%20The%20company%20needs%20to%20nail%20productivity%20%E2%80%94%20primarily%20on%20the%20business%20side%2C%20and%20then%20on%20the%20consumer%20side%2C%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BEverything%20else%20is%20going%20to%20have%20to%20take%20a%20backseat%20to%20those%20priorities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20announcement%20came%20three%20months%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-openai-licensing-deal-ai-characters-sora-chatgpt-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDisney%20announced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20would%20become%20the%20first%20major%20content%20license%20holder%20with%20OpenAI%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20three-year%20deal%20that%20included%20a%20%241%20billion%20investment%20in%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-openai-licensing-deal-ai-characters-sora-chatgpt-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EDisney%20announced%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20would%20become%20the%20first%20major%20content%20license%20holder%20on%20the%20platform%20as%20part%20of%20a%20three-year%20deal%20that%20included%20a%20%241%20billion%20investment%20in%20OpenAI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDisney%20acknowledged%20OpenAI's%20move%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20nascent%20AI%20field%20advances%20rapidly%2C%20we%20respect%20OpenAI's%20decision%20to%20exit%20the%20video%20generation%20business%20and%20to%20shift%20its%20priorities%20elsewhere%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20from%20The%20Walt%20Disney%20Company%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20appreciate%20the%20constructive%20collaboration%20between%20our%20teams%20and%20what%20we%20learned%20from%20it%2C%20and%20we%20will%20continue%20to%20engage%20with%20AI%20platforms%20to%20find%20new%20ways%20to%20meet%20fans%20where%20they%20are%20while%20responsibly%20embracing%20new%20technologies%20that%20respect%20IP%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20creators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20quickly%20made%20moves%20to%20try%20to%20monetize%20Sora's%20growing%20user%20base%20and%20to%20limit%20free%20video%20generations.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Peebles%2C%20in%20posts%20on%20X%2C%20framed%20the%20economics%20of%20the%20heavy%20demand%20for%20Sora%20as%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20unsustainable%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3Bvideo%20models%20really%20are%20expensive!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-discontinues-sora-video-app-amid-robotics-shift-compute-limitations-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774386318000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2f2925b58f1f0f9336c36%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-discontinues-sora-video-app-amid-robotics-shift-compute-limitations-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20spokesperson%20for%20OpenAI%20said%20the%20discontinuation%20of%20Sora%20comes%20as%20the%20company%20plans%20to%20focus%20on%20robotics%20rather%20than%20generative%20imagery.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktl%40businessinsider.com%20(Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert%2CBrent%20D.%20Griffiths)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-discontinues-sora-video-app-amid-robotics-shift-compute-limitations-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Judge%20says%20it%20looks%20like%20Pentagon%20was%20out%20to%20'punish'%20Anthropic%2C%20not%20protect%20national%20security%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20composite%20image%20of%20Dario%20Amodei%20and%20Pete%20Hegseth%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2a46e5b58f1f0f9336958%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnthropic%20CEO%20Dario%20Amodei%20refused%20to%20accede%20to%20Defense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth's%20demands%2C%20which%20eventually%20led%20to%20the%20legal%20fight.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAnthropic%20has%20asked%20a%20judge%20to%20block%20the%20Pentagon%20from%20labeling%20it%20a%20supply%20chain%20risk.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20label%20could%20prevent%20Anthropic%20from%20getting%20lucrative%20government%20contracts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20a%20federal%20judge%20called%20the%20Department%20of%20War's%20label%20%26quot%3Btroubling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20federal%20judge%20in%20San%20Francisco%20lit%20into%20the%20Pentagon%20on%20Tuesday%20for%20its%20attempt%20to%20blacklist%20Anthropic%20following%20a%20dispute%20over%20its%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20looks%20like%20an%20attempt%20to%20cripple%20Anthropic%2C%26quot%3B%20Judge%20Rita%20Lin%20said%20at%20a%20hearing%20on%20Tuesday%20to%20decide%20whether%20the%20government's%20%26quot%3Bsupply%20chain%20risk%26quot%3B%20label%20can%20stand%20while%20Anthropic's%20case%20against%20the%20Department%20of%20War%20proceeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%203%2C%20Defense%20Secretary%20Peter%20Hegseth%20formally%20notified%20Anthropic%20that%20he%20was%20labeling%20the%20company%20and%20its%20products%20as%20a%20supply%20chain%20risk%2C%20the%20first%20time%20such%20a%20designation%20had%20been%20applied%20to%20a%20US%20company.%20The%20designation%20is%20akin%20to%20putting%20Anthropic%2C%20the%20maker%20of%20Claude%2C%20on%20a%20government%20blacklist%2C%20restricting%20both%20its%20contracts%20and%20how%20its%20technology%20can%20be%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20action%2C%20Anthropic%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdario-amodei%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDario%20Amodei%20%3C%2Fa%3Epublicly%20announced%20that%20he%20would%20not%20agree%20to%20Hegseth's%20demands%20for%20the%20Pentagon%20to%20have%20unfettered%20access%20to%20its%20AI%20models%20%26quot%3Bfor%20any%20lawful%20use.%26quot%3B%20Amodei%20said%20he%20was%20concerned%20that%20a%20contract%20with%20that%20language%20could%20allow%20for%20misuse%20in%20surveilling%20Americans%20or%20lead%20to%20Anthropic's%20AI%20being%20deployed%20in%20fully%20autonomous%20weapons%20before%20it%20was%20safe%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELin%2C%20who%20has%20handled%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-poaching-trade-secrets-lawsuit-openai-judge-dismiss-ruling-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehigh-profile%20tech%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20the%20decision%20to%20label%20Anthropic%20as%20a%20supply%20chain%20risk%20was%20%26quot%3Btroubling%26quot%3B%20given%20that%20the%20designation%20is%20normally%20reserved%20for%20%26quot%3Badversaries%20of%20the%20US%20government%20who%20may%20sabotage%20its%20technology%20systems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDOW%20could%20just%20stop%20using%20Claude%2C%26quot%3B%20Lin%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20The%20Department%20of%20War%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20preferred%20name%20for%20the%20Pentagon.%20%26quot%3BIt%20looks%20like%20they%20went%20further%20than%20that%20because%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20punish%20Anthropic.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELin%20said%20that%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20separate%20order%20posted%20on%20Truth%20Social%2C%20ordering%20every%20federal%20agency%20to%20cease%20using%20Anthropic%20within%20six%20months%2C%20was%20so%20broad%20that%20it%20could%20apply%20to%20agencies%20far%20outside%20the%20national%20security%20realm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20that%20would%20include%20the%20National%20Endowment%20for%20the%20Arts%20using%20Claude%20to%20design%20its%20website%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnthropic%20sued%20to%20block%20Hegseth's%20action%20and%20Trump's%20order.%20Tuesday's%20hearing%20was%20scheduled%20for%20the%20judge%20to%20hear%20arguments%20over%20whether%20she%20should%20lift%20the%20ban%20until%20the%20case%20goes%20to%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20legal%20filings%2C%20Anthropic%20said%20the%20designation%20was%20%26quot%3Bjeopardizing%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20the%20near-term%26quot%3B%20because%20of%20the%20uncertainty%20around%20what%20it%20meant%20for%20defense%20contractors%20that%20also%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-ai-tools-tech-selloff-software-apocalypse-cybersecurity-anthropic-ibm-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EClaude%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20top%20of%20those%20immediate%20economic%20harms%2C%20Anthropic's%20reputation%20and%20core%20First%20Amendment%20freedoms%20are%20under%20attack%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20AI%20startup's%20lawyers%20wrote%20in%20their%20complaint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeputy%20Assistant%20Attorney%20General%20Eric%20Hamilton%2C%20who%20argued%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20administration%2C%20said%20that%20Lin%20did%20not%20need%20to%20block%20Hegseth's%20order%20because%20the%20Justice%20Department%20has%20%26quot%3Bclarified%26quot%3B%20Hegseth's%20Feburary%2027th%20directive%20post%20on%20X%20that%20suggested%20that%20even%20contractors%20who%20used%20Anthropic's%20products%20for%20non-defense%20uses%20might%20cease%20their%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamilton%20said%20the%20Pentagon%20is%20not%20concerned%20about%20%26quot%3Bnon-DOW%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamilton%20said%20the%20supply%20chain%20risk%20designation%20must%20also%20remain%20because%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bfuture%20risk%26quot%3B%20of%20how%20Anthropic%20could%20update%20its%20models%20in%20a%20way%20the%20Pentagon%20objects%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESilicon%20Valley%20is%20closely%20watching%20the%20case%20because%20a%20broad%20interpretation%20of%20the%20Pentagon's%20restrictions%20could%20ripple%20out%20to%20partners%20like%20Microsoft%2C%20which%20filed%20an%20amicus%20brief%20supporting%20Anthropic.%20As%20a%20government%20contractor%2C%20Microsoft%20could%20be%20forced%20to%20limit%20how%20it%20uses%20Anthropic's%20Claude.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20broadly%2C%20the%20case%20will%20test%20how%20far%20the%20federal%20government%20can%20go%20in%20restricting%20AI%20vendors%20through%20its%20contracting%20and%20national%20security%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-supply-chain-risk-hearing-judge-pentagon-pubish-cripple-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774385874000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c2a51058b5806618e7dc9f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-supply-chain-risk-hearing-judge-pentagon-pubish-cripple-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anthropic%20has%20sued%20to%20stop%20Defense%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20from%20labeling%20the%20company%20a%20risk%20after%20it%20set%20limits%20on%20the%20use%20of%20its%20technology.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-supply-chain-risk-hearing-judge-pentagon-pubish-cripple-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20happened%20in%20the%20seconds%20before%20Air%20Canada%20plane%20crashed%20at%20LaGuardia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774385758000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F1b3d%2Flive%2F8e0056b0-27a5-11f1-934f-036468834728.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fvideos%2Fc70584eye0no%233%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22BBC%20Verify%20breaks%20down%20the%20moments%20before%20the%2